---
# mem-vault per-project configuration
# Copy this file to .claude/mem-vault.local.md and edit as needed.
# Not committed by default (covered by .gitignore pattern ".claude/*.local.md").

# Override vault data directory (default: %USERPROFILE%\.mem-vault)
# vault_dir: "D:/vaults/mem-vault"

# Comma-separated list of tool names to NEVER capture (default captures Edit|Write|NotebookEdit|Bash|Task)
# capture_excludes: TodoWrite,Glob,Grep

# Trim body text to N characters when capturing (default 2000)
# max_body_chars: 2000

# Skip capturing bash commands matching any of these regexes (JSON array)
# bash_ignore_patterns: ["^(ls|pwd|cd|echo)", "^git status"]

# Files whose edits should never be captured (secrets, build artifacts, etc.)
# never_capture_paths: [".env*", "*.pem", "node_modules/**", "dist/**"]
---

# Project-scoped notes for mem-vault

Free-form markdown below the frontmatter is ignored by the plugin but useful for
human documentation of what this project's memory contains and any manual
maintenance notes.
